{
  "texts": [
    "Natural zeolite is mainly composed of silicon dioxide, while the synthetic variant, known as Fluid Catalytic Cracking (FCC) zeolite, is a by-product of the petrochemical industry, rich in aluminum oxide.",
    "FCC zeolite, originating from the fluid catalytic cracking process, is often more contaminated, which leads to its classification as a waste material.",
    "In a study by fode et al. [28], both types of zeolites were utilized as high volume SCMs in ordinary Portland cement mortar.",
    "The zeolites were incorporated at levels ranging from 25 to 50%, with an additional 10% of lime added to supply extra calcium.",
    "The purpose of adding lime was to speed up the hydration process, thereby improving the setting time and enhancing the overall efficiency of the concrete mixture."
  ]
}